## Summary
Created and configured user accounts in Microsoft Entra ID, including properties like job title, department, and usage location.

Invited an external guest user to join your tenant and confirmed the invitation process.

Created a security group called IT Lab Administrators, set membership type to Assigned, and added both internal and external users.

Explored tenant management features such as licenses, password reset, and navigation in the Azure portal.

Reviewed group settings like expiration, naming policies, and ownership assignment.

## Key concepts
Tenant: A dedicated instance of Microsoft Entra ID representing your organization, containing accounts and groups.

User Accounts: Can be internal (employees) or external (guests). Each account has properties that define access and identity.

Groups:

Security groups → used for access control.

Microsoft 365 groups → used for collaboration.

Membership Types:

Static (Assigned) → admins manually add/remove members.

Dynamic → membership updates automatically based on user properties (requires Entra ID Premium P1/P2).

Governance: Owners manage groups, expiration policies enforce lifecycle, and naming policies ensure consistency.

